I"<h1 id="origano-tomato-tuna-pasta">Origano-tomato tuna pasta</h1>

<p>Letâ€™s see how to cook your chosen dish.</p>

<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>

<p>Here is what you need to have at home.</p>

<ol>
  <li>4 cans, tuna, in oil</li>
  <li>2, onions, finely chopped</li>
  <li>3 cloves, garlic, grated</li>
  <li>250 g,  penne pasta</li>
  <li>1 can, chopped tomato, or 1 tube, tomato puree</li>
  <li>2 TBSPs, ketchup</li>
  <li>1 glass, white wine</li>
  <li>Herbs: 1 handfull of origano and parsley</li>
  <li>Seasoning: salt, pepper and paprika powder</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="preparation">Preparation</h2>

<p>Here are the steps to cook the meal. Enjoy!</p>

<ol>
  <li>Start playing music in the background.</li>
  <li>Pore a glass of drink for the chef.</li>
  <li>Finely chop the onions and chuck it in a sauce pan. Sprinkle the oil on the onion from the tuna cans. Start frying.</li>
  <li>Add a bit of paprika to the onions and load the tuna on. Stir it. Add the seasoning to it.</li>
  <li>Add the white wine and boil the alcohol away.</li>
  <li>add the tomato puree, ketchup and the herbs. Grate the garlic on the mixture.</li>
  <li>Boil the penne for 8 minutes, then mix the tuna and the pasta in a bowl.</li>
  <li>Serve it with cheese.</li>
</ol>

